# Test before deploy (API / outreach / functions)

**Never upload or deploy backend changes until the matching tests pass locally.**

## Hosting outreach (`api-carlxaeron/hosting-php/`)

Any edit to `src/outreach.php`, mail helpers, cron scripts, or cadence/max-follow-up logic:

```bash
php api-carlxaeron/hosting-php/tests/run-unit.php
```

Must exit **0**. Only then `hosting_upload` / sync to Stellar.

Sequence under test: **3d → 7d → 7d → 7d**, max **4** follow-ups (`cadence: 3d1w`).

## Laravel API (`api-carlxaeron/`)

```bash
cd api-carlxaeron && php artisan test
```

Required before deploying Laravel app files to `public_html/api-carlxaeron/`.

## Firebase Cloud Functions (`functions/`)

```bash
cd functions && npm test
```

If no test script exists yet, run at least a syntax/load check (`node -c` / require smoke) and say so — then add tests when touching non-trivial logic. Prefer `npm test` once defined.

Required before `firebase deploy --only functions` / `npm run deploy`.

## Agent checklist

```
Backend deploy gate:
- [ ] Identify which surface changed (hosting-php / Laravel / functions)
- [ ] Run the matching unit/feature tests — all green
- [ ] Only then deploy (hosting-ssh upload or Firebase)
- [ ] Smoke: curl https://api.carlmanuel.com/health (API) or functions smoke the agent already uses
```

## Do not

- Deploy broken cadence/maxFollowUps changes without updating `tests/run-unit.php` expectations
- Skip outreach unit tests “just for a small fix” on `outreach.php`
- Ship hosting cron script changes without re-running unit tests
